Phase 0 — C++ prerequisite (`@c++ developer`)
- [ ] Update the C++ image-resizing app for profile-picture use case.
- [ ] Define/implement C++ resize API arguments expected from Java backend: `targetWidth`, `targetHeight`, `maxBytes`, `canCrop`, `keepAspectRatio`.
- [ ] Validate expected resize output and runtime compatibility for JNI integration.
- [ ] Mark prerequisite complete before starting Phase 4 and backend JNI wiring.

Phase 1 — Contracts and API boundaries (`@backend-dev` + `@business-analyst`)
- [ ] Define request/response contract for `CID-LOGIN-PROFILE-UPLOAD` and `CID-MBOOK-PROFILEPICTURE-UPDATE`.
- [ ] Add/refresh entries in `.github/references/CONTRACTS_INDEX.md`.
- [ ] Update module READMEs with endpoint behavior.

Phase 2 — dalogin authenticated upload gateway (`@backend-dev` + `@security-specialist`)
- [ ] Add `POST /login/profile-picture` endpoint with existing auth/session filters.
- [ ] Validate multipart metadata and forward payload to `mbook`.
- [ ] Preserve X-Token/Ciphertext/XSRF context through proxy path.

Phase 3 — mbook profile picture endpoint (`@backend-dev` + `@database-dev`)
- [ ] Add `POST /rest/user/profile-picture` endpoint in `mbook`.
- [ ] Validate file type/size and sanitize filename.
- [ ] Update `Logins.profilePicture` only after successful storage.

Phase 4 — OpenCV JNI integration (`@c++ developer` + `@backend-dev`)
- [ ] Add JNI bridge layer for resize operation.
- [ ] Pass Java backend resize arguments end-to-end into native layer (`targetWidth`, `targetHeight`, `maxBytes`, `canCrop`, `keepAspectRatio`).
- [ ] Compile/package native library for runtime image service path.
- [ ] Add controlled fallback/error handling when native load fails.

Phase 5 — PVC storage and runtime wiring (`@devops` + `@backend-dev`)
- [ ] Ensure `/pictures/profiles` is mounted and writable in relevant service.
- [ ] Verify files are persistent and copyable via `kubectl cp`.
- [ ] Document mount/runtime behavior in `k8infra/README-k8s-local.md`.

Phase 6 — iOS integration (`@ios-dev`)
- [ ] Add upload/change profile action in `MenuVC`.
- [ ] Add networking call through `dalogin` upload endpoint.
- [ ] Refresh user profile view after upload success.

Phase 7 — Verification (`@testing-engineer` + `@security-specialist` + `@performance-engineer`)
- [ ] Add integration tests for success + invalid file type + oversize file.
- [ ] Add smoke test for end-to-end upload and profile readback.
- [ ] Validate auth/XSRF enforcement and path traversal protection.
- [ ] Record resize/upload latency baseline.

